|22 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Djelfa Province|Djelfa]]\n|26 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Gharda\u00efa Province|Gharda\u00efa]]\n|26 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Laghouat Province|Laghouat]]\n|24 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tissemsilt Province|Tissemsilt]]\n|19 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n\n!'''Total'''\n! \n!716\n!44\n!37\n|-class=\"sortbottom\"\n|colspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <small>Latest update: 31 March 2020 (source: [http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/carte/ covid19]<ref>{{cite web|title=Carte \u00e9pid\u00e9miologique|url=http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/carte/|language=fr|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref></small>)\n|}\n\n==See also== \n{{Div col}}\n*[[2020 in Algeria]]\n* [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]]\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tunisia]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation and tourism]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tunisia}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Morocco}}\n{{#related:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Algeria]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Algeria]]\n[[Category:2020 in Algeria]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Algeria]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Africa]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Algeria}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Algeria\n| map1            = Algeria_Coronavirus_cases_by_province.png\n| legend1         = {{legend|#8B0000|20+ Confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#d40000|5-19 Confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#FF9999|1-4 Confirmed cases}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Algeria]]\n| first_case      = [[Blida]]\n| arrival_date    = 17 February 2020 <br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=2|day1=17|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases  = 37 (31 March 2020)\n| deaths          = 44 (31 March 2020)\n| confirmed_cases = 716 (31 March 2020)\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/carte/\nhttp://covid19.cipalgerie.com/en/\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Algeria]] in February 2020.\n__TOC__\n\n== Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Algeria medical cases chart}}\nOn 25 February, Algeria laboratory-confirmed its first case of [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), an Italian man who arrived on 17 February;<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://africatimes.com/2020/02/25/algerian-health-minister-confirms-first-covid-19-case/|title=Algerian health minister confirms first COVID-19 case|date=25 February 2020}}</ref> on 28 February, Algeria deported him back to Italy, via a special flight from [[Oued Irara\u2013Krim Belkacem Airport|Hassi Messaoud Airport]] where he was subject to quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://echoroukonline.com/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%8A%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A8%D9%83%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86/|title=\u062a\u0631\u062d\u064a\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0627\u0637\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0637\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0635\u0627\u0628 \u0628\u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 | date= February 2020|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March, Algeria confirmed two new cases of SARS-CoV-2, a woman and her daughter, the health ministry said.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200301233025-scjao/|title=Algeria confirms two more coronavirus cases|date=2 March 2020|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302013223/https://news.trust.org/item/20200301233025-scjao/|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn the afternoon of 3 March, Algeria reported another two new cases of SARS-CoV-2, which brought the total number of confirmed cases to five, a state news agency said quoting a statement from the health ministry. The statement added that the two new cases are from the same family, a father and daughter, and were living in France, adding that there's an investigation to determine the identities of the people who were in contact with them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-algeria-idUSKBN20P2YK|title=Algeria reports two new coronavirus cases, bringing the total to five|date=2 March 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=2 March 2020|language=en}}</ref> The Ministry of Health announced on the evening of 3 March that three new cases of SARS-CoV-2 had been registered in Algeria, all from the same family, bringing the total number of cases to eight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ennaharonline.com/%d8%a7%d8%b1%d8%aa%d9%81%d8%a7%d8%b9-%d8%b9%d8%af%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a5%d8%b5%d8%a7%d8%a8%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%a4%d9%83%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%a8%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%b1%d9%88%d8%b3-%d9%83%d9%88/|title=\u0627\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0635\u0627\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0624\u0643\u062f\u0629 \u0628\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0625\u0644\u0649 8 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0627\u062a|date=3 March 2020|website=\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|language=ar|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> On 4 March, the Ministry of Health recorded 4 new confirmed cases of SARS-CoV-2, from the same family, bringing the total number of cases to 12.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ennaharonline.com/%d8%a7%d8%b1%d8%aa%d9%81%d8%a7%d8%b9-%d8%b9%d8%af%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a5%d8%b5%d8%a7%d8%a8%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%a4%d9%83%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%a8%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%b1%d9%88%d8%b3-%d9%83%d9%88-2/|title=\u0627\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0635\u0627\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0624\u0643\u062f\u0629 \u0628\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0625\u0644\u0649 12 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0629|date=4 March 2020|website=\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|language=ar|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn the evening of 12 March, Algeria reported a new case in [[Ain Smara]], and schools were locked due to coronavirus spread in Algeria.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 7 March, a 20th case, an Algerian who had stayed in Spain was announced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsa-algerie.com/derniere-minute-deux-nouveaux-cas-de-coronavirus-en-algerie-19-au-total/|title=Deux nouveaux cas de coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie, 19 au total|date=7 March 2020|website=TSA|language=fr|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/08/coronavirus-un-nouveau-cas-enregistre-20-au-total-en-algerie/|title=Coronavirus : un nouveau cas enregistr\u00e9, 20 au total en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Mehenni|first=Ouramdane|date=8 March 2020|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, five new cases of COVID-19, including one death, aged 78 and placed in isolation at [[Blida hospital]]. Two cases having stayed in France, one in the [[Souk Ahras Province|Souk-Ahras province]], the other in the [[Tizi Ouzou Province|Tizi-Ouzou province]] and three in that of [[Blida Province|Blida province]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsa-algerie.com/coronavirus-premier-deces-en-algerie-deux-nouvelles-wilayas-touchees/|title=Coronavirus : premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie, deux nouvelles wilayas touch\u00e9es|date=12 March 2020|website=TSA|language=fr|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> the total number of confirmed cases is 26 adding a woman in the wilaya of [[Skikda]] having stayed in France was announced, and a second death aged 55 is recorded without indication of the place of residence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/urgent-coronavirus-en-algerie-deuxieme-deces-en-algerie/|title=Urgent {{!}} Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Deuxi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=12 March 2020|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ennaharonline.com/%d8%a5%d8%b1%d8%aa%d9%81%d8%a7%d8%b9-%d8%b9%d8%af%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d8%b5%d8%a7%d8%a8%d9%8a%d9%86-%d8%a8%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%b1%d9%88%d8%b3-%d9%83%d9%88/|title=\u0625\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0641\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0635\u0627\u0628\u064a\u0646 \u0628\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0625\u0644\u0649 \u0625\u062b\u0646\u064a\u0646|date=12 March 2020|website=\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|language=ar|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, a new case confirmed in [[Algiers]], a 36-year-old Algerian who stayed in France.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/13/coronavirus-nouveau-cas-conforme-algerie-1er-cas-alger/|title=Coronavirus : Un nouveau cas confirm\u00e9 en Alg\u00e9rie, le 1er cas \u00e0 Alger|last=AE|first=R\u00e9daction|date=13 March 2020|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, the Algerian's [[Ministry of Health (Algeria)|Ministry of Health]] announced 10 new confirmed cases with the COVID-19 coronavirus and one death. This is the third death that resides in [[Blida]]. It is a 51-year-old woman from Blida. With this new case, the total number of cases registered in Algeria reached 37 confirmed cases and 3 deaths. The ministry also said 12 confirmed cases left containment after healing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-10-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-et-un-deces/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : 10 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s et un d\u00e9c\u00e8s (MAJ) - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=14 March 2020|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dzairdaily.com/coronavirus-algerie-bilan-3-mort-37-cas-confirme-covid-19/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Bilan de 3 morts, 37 cas confirm\u00e9s|date=14 March 2020|website=Dzair Daily|language=fr-FR|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, [[Prime Minister of Algeria|The Prime Minister]] [[Abdelaziz Djerad]] said that \"45 cases have been confirmed by the [[Pasteur Institute of Algiers|Pasteur Institute of Algeria]] ...\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.observalgerie.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-le-nombre-de-cas-testes-positifs-augmente-a-45/2020/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Le nombre de cas contamin\u00e9s augmente|date=15 March 2020|website=Observ'Alg\u00e9rie|language=fr-FR|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/15/coronavirus-le-nombre-de-cas-confirmes-passe-a-45/|title=Coronavirus: Le nombre de cas confirm\u00e9s passe \u00e0 45|last=A|first=Imene|date=15 March 2020|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> Eleven new cases of contamination with the coronavirus were confirmed, including one (1) death, a woman aged 84 years in the wilaya of Blida, the total number of cases recorded in Algeria reached forty-eight (48) confirmed cases and four (4) deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dzvid.com/2020/03/15/alerte-48-cas-de-coronavirus-et-4-deces-en-algerie/|title=Alerte : 48 cas de coronavirus et 4 d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie !|last=Guatri|first=Am\u00e9lia|date=15 March 2020|website=DzVID|language=fr-FR|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jijel.info/index.php/national/7240-coronavirus-48-cas-confirmes-par-l-institut-pasteur|title=jijel.info - Coronavirus: 48 cas confirm\u00e9s par l'Institut Pasteur|website=www.jijel.info|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> In the evening, a new confirmed case was registered in the [[Adrar Province]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-un-cas-confirme-a-adrar/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Un cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Adrar - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=15 March 2020|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, six new confirmed cases of COVID-19, these are two cases in Algiers, one case in the [[Bouira Province]], one case in the [[Bordj Bou Arr\u00e9ridj Province]], one case in the [[Tizi Ouzou Province]] and a case in the [[Annaba Province]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/sante-science-technologie/103110-covid-19-six-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-soixante-au-total|title=Covid-19: six nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s, soixante au total|last=Nassima|first=Dib|website=www.aps.dz|language=fr-fr|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, a fifth death was recorded in the Blida Province, a 51-year-old man with [[chronic condition]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/17/coronavirus-cinquieme-deces-en-algerie/|title=Coronavirus: Cinqui\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Litamine|first=Khelifa|date=17 March 2020|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> In the B\u00e9ja\u00efa Province, a first confirmed case.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/17/coronavirus-premier-cas-confirme-a-bejaia/|title=Coronavirus : Premier cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Bejaia|last=Benali|first=Arezki|date=17 March 2020|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> and a case in the  Skikda Province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-un-nouveau-cas-enregistre-a-skikda/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : un nouveau cas enregistr\u00e9 \u00e0 Skikda - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=2020-03-17|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, a sixth death was registered in the Blida Province, a 62-year-old man died on 17 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.observalgerie.com/coronavirus-lalgerie-enregistre-un-6eme-deces/2020/|title=Coronavirus : L'Alg\u00e9rie enregistre un 6\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s|date=2020-03-18|website=Observ'Alg\u00e9rie|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> eight new cases bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 75.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/18/coronavirus-un-bilan-de-75-cas-7-deces-et-32-patients-gueris-en-algerie/|title=Coronavirus : Un bilan de 75 cas, 7 d\u00e9c\u00e8s et 32 patients gu\u00e9ris en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Benali|first=Arezki|date=2020-03-18|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Another new death (7th) in [[El Oued Province]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-deux-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-a-oued-souf/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : deux nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Oued Souf - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=2020-03-18|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, ten new confirmed cases of the COVID-19, including two new deaths, to reach a total of 82 confirmed cases including eight deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://covid19.sante.gov.dz/fr/2020/03/19/suivi-quotidien-du-coronavirus-covid-19-jeudi-19-mars-2020/|title=Suivi quotidien du Coronavirus COVID-19 Jeudi 19 mars 2020 \u2013 Minist\u00e8re de la Sant\u00e9 de la Population et de la R\u00e9forme Hospitali\u00e8re avec la contribution du Minist\u00e8re de la Poste et des T\u00e9l\u00e9communications|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> The same day, a ninth death is recorded in the [[M\u00e9d\u00e9a Province]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.observalgerie.com/coronavirus-lalgerie-enregistre-un-neuvieme-deces/2020/|title=Coronavirus : L'Alg\u00e9rie enregistre un neuvi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s|date=2020-03-19|website=Observ'Alg\u00e9rie|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> a 47-year-old man (Former Algerian judo player Othman Tijani)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beurfm.net/news/coronavirus-deces-du-judoka-algerien-othman-tijani-21135|title=Coronavirus : d\u00e9c\u00e8s du judoka alg\u00e9rien Othman Tijani - Beur FM|website=www.beurfm.net|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.saudi24.news/2020/03/the-death-of-an-algerian-athlete-with-corona-virus-sport-arab-and-international.html|title=The death of an Algerian athlete with Corona virus \u2013 sport \u2013 Arab and international|last=admin|date=2020-03-20|website=Saudi 24 News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellerreport.com/sports/2020-03-19---the-first-athlete-in-algeria-died-of-the-corona-virus-.Sylob7B-UI.html|title=The first athlete in Algeria died of the Corona virus {{!}} tellerreport.com|last=Anonym|website=www.tellerreport.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, a tenth death was recorded in Algeria in [[El Oued Province]], it is the sister of the first case of Province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ennaharonline.com/%d8%aa%d8%b3%d8%ac%d9%8a%d9%84-%d8%ad%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a9-%d9%88%d9%81%d8%a7%d8%a9-%d8%ac%d8%af%d9%8a%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%a8%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%b1%d9%88%d8%b3-%d9%83%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%88%d9%86%d8%a7-%d9%81%d9%8a-2/|title=\u062a\u0633\u062c\u064a\u0644 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0648\u0641\u0627\u0629 \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0628\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0635\u064a\u0644\u0629 \u062a\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0639 \u0625\u0644\u0649 10|date=2020-03-20|website=\u0627\u0644\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|language=ar|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-un-deuxieme-deces-a-el-oued/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Un deuxi\u00e8me d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 El Oued - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=2020-03-20|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> The death (11th) of a 77-year-old woman  has been announced in [[Azeffoun]], [[Tizi Ouzou Province|Tizi-Ouzou Province]], bringing the death toll from the virus to 11 in Algeria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.echoroukonline.com/%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%b1%d9%88%d8%b3-%d9%83%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%88%d9%86%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d8%b1%d8%aa%d9%81%d8%a7%d8%b9-%d8%b9%d8%af%d8%af-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%88%d9%81%d9%8a%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d9%81%d9%8a-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%ac/|title=\u0641\u064a\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u0643\u0648\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627: \u0627\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0641\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u0627\u0626\u0631 \u0625\u0644\u0649 11 \u062d\u0627\u0644\u0627\u062a|date=2020-03-20|website=\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0642 \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|language=ar|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/20/coronavirus-premier-deces-enregistre-a-tizi-ouzou/|title=Coronavirus : Premier d\u00e9c\u00e8s enregistr\u00e9 \u00e0 Tizi-Ouzou|last=Litamine|first=Khelifa|date=2020-03-20|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref> and another (12 th) in [[Khenchela Province]], an 85-year-old man.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-un-nouveau-cas-de-deces-a-khenchela/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : Un nouveau cas de d\u00e9c\u00e8s \u00e0 Khenchela - Alg\u00e9rie360.com|date=2020-03-20|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> [[2019-20 Algerian protests|Anti-government protests]] were called off for the first time in over a year.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-algeria-protests-called-off-183710607.html Coronavirus: Algeria protests called off for first time in a year] BBC, 20 March 2020</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, the balance sheet was 139 confirmed cases, including 78 in the  Blida Province, 6 in [[Oran Province]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-5-nouveau-cas-confirmes-a-oran/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : 5 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Oran - Algerie360|date=2020-03-21|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> and a first confirmed case in [[Relizane Province]] 46.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie360.com/coronavirus-en-algerie-1er-cas-confirme-a-relizane/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : 1er cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Relizane - Algerie360|date=2020-03-21|website=www.algerie360.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> 15 deaths, including eight deaths in the wilaya of Blida Province.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/sante-science-technologie/103290-coronavirus-139-cas-confirmes-dont-15-deces-en-algerie|title=Coronavirus: 139 cas confirm\u00e9s, dont 15 d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Mounia|first=Boudjedri|website=www.aps.dz|language=fr-fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, the Algerian Minister of Health, Abderrahmane Benbouzid, announced that \"Algeria has entered the third phase of the coronavirus epidemic and, therefore, we must prepare for the worst\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsa-algerie.com/lalgerie-est-entree-en-phase-3-du-coronavirus-on-doit-se-preparer-au-pire/|title=Coronavirus : l'Alg\u00e9rie est entr\u00e9e en Phase 3|date=2020-03-22|website=TSA|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref> The assessment of the day according to the Commission for monitoring the evolution of the epidemic, amounted to 201 confirmed cases and 17 deaths. 62 confirmed cases and two additional deaths compared to the last assessment. The two new deaths are recorded, one in the wilaya of [[Bejaia Province|B\u00e9ja\u00efa Province]], an 82-year-old man and the other in Khenchela province, an 85-year-old man.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsa-algerie.com/nouveau-bilan-en-algerie-17-morts-et-201-cas-confirmes/|title=Nouveau bilan en Alg\u00e9rie : 17 morts et 201 cas confirm\u00e9s|date=2020-03-22|website=TSA|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, the balance sheet was 230 confirmed cases and 17 deaths, including 125 confirmed cases in Blida Province. 25 provinces are affected by the pandemic in Algeria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tsa-algerie.com/alerte-nouveau-bilan-230-cas-confirmes-aucun-nouveau-deces/|title=Covid-19, nouveau bilan en Alg\u00e9rie : 230 cas, aucun nouveau d\u00e9c\u00e8s|date=2020-03-23|website=TSA|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the balance is of 264 confirmed cases and 19 deaths, after recording 34 new cases according to the revelations of the spokesperson of the Scientific Committee for monitoring the evolution of the Coronavirus pandemic, Djamel Fourar. The two death cases concern a 72-year-old man and that of a 70-year-old immigrant, registered respectively in Tizi-Ouzou and Boumerd\u00e9s Provinces.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/en/health-science-technology/33708-coronavirus-34-further-cases-confirmed-including-two-deaths-in-algeria|title=Coronavirus: 34 further cases confirmed, including two deaths in Algeria|last=SLIMANI|first=KARIMA|website=www.aps.dz|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/algerie/103375-trente-quatre-34-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-dont-deux-02-deces-en-algerie|title=\u0650Covid 19: Trente-quatre nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s, dont deux d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Hafiane|first=Badra|website=www.aps.dz|language=fr-fr|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, 38 new confirmed cases and two new deaths. The two new deaths are recorded, one in [[Tipaza Province]], a man aged 45 years and the other in the [[Constantine Province]], a woman aged 58 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/sante-science-technologie/103409-coronavirus-38-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-dont-deux-deces-en-algerie|title=Coronavirus: 38 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s, dont deux d\u00e9c\u00e8s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=SLIMANI|first=KARIMA|website=www.aps.dz|language=fr-fr|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/25/coronavirus-en-algerie-le-bilan-monte-a-302-cas-confirmes-dont-21-morts/|title=Coronavirus en Alg\u00e9rie : 302 cas confirm\u00e9s dont 21 morts|last=Litamine|first=Khelifa|date=2020-03-25|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, 65 new confirmed cases and four new deaths were recorded, bringing the number of confirmed cases to 367 and the number of deaths to 25''',''' The four new deaths are recorded, two in the Constantine Province, a man aged 90 years and a woman of 58 years, a death in the wilaya of Tizi Ouzou Province, a woman aged 53 years and a death in Blida Province, an ambulance driver in the Boufarik hospital.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/en/health-science-technology/33727-coronavirus-65-new-confirmed-cases-4-deaths-in-algeria|title=Coronavirus: 65 new confirmed cases, 4 deaths in Algeria|last=Farid|first=Nemoura|website=www.aps.dz|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.algerie-eco.com/2020/03/26/coronavirus-367-cas-confirmes-et-quatre-nouveaux-deces-enregistres-en-algerie/|title=Coronavirus: 367 cas confirm\u00e9s et quatre nouveaux d\u00e9c\u00e8s enregistr\u00e9s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Litamine|first=Khelifa|date=2020-03-26|website=Algerie Eco|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, 42 new confirmed cases, including one death have been reported during the last 24 hours in Algeria, bringing the number of confirmed cases to 409 and that of deaths to 26, are spread across thirty-six (36) provinces, including 180 in Blida, which represents 44% of the global number of infected people.The new death is registered in [[Bordj Bou Arr\u00e9ridj Province|Bordj Bou Arreridj province]], a 71-year-old woman.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/en/health-science-technology/33734-coronavirus-42-new-confirmed-cases-one-more-death-in-algeria|title=Coronavirus: 42 new confirmed cases, one more death in Algeria|last=Saci|first=Yasmine|website=www.aps.dz|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/algerie/103468-coronavirus-42-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-et-un-autre-deces-enregistres-en-algerie|title=Coronavirus : 42 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s et un autre d\u00e9c\u00e8s enregistr\u00e9s en Alg\u00e9rie|last=Hafiane|first=Badra|website=www.aps.dz|language=fr-fr|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, 45 new confirmed cases and three new deaths were recorded. The deaths consist in a man aged 65 years from Algiers, a man aged 84 years from M\u00e9d\u00e9a and a man aged 45 years from [[Mostaganem Province]], the latter came after a visit from Spain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/en/health-science-technology/33742-coronavirus-45-new-confirmed-cases-three-deaths-in-algeria|title=Coronavirus: 45 new confirmed cases, three deaths in Algeria|last=SLIMANI|first=KARIMA|website=www.aps.dz|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, a total of 57 new cases and two \u00a0deaths have been recorded in the last 24 hours in Algeria, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 511 and of deaths to 31.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aps.dz/en/health-science-technology/33750-coronavirus-57-new-confirmed-cases-two-deaths-in-algeria|title=Coronavirus: 57 new confirmed cases, two deaths in Algeria|last=Sidhoum|first=Samira|website=www.aps.dz|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Location of cases ==\n{| class=\"wikitable centre alternance sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Province\n!scope=\"col\"| First case\n!scope=\"col\"| Confirmed cases\n!scope=\"col\"| Deaths\n!scope=\"col\"| Recoveries\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Blida Province|Blida]]\n| 1 March 2020\n| 252\n| 10\n| 27\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Algiers Province|Algiers]]\n| 13 March 2020\n| 65\n| 4\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Oran Province|Oran]]\n|21 March 2020\n|16\n|2\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tizi Ouzou Province|Tizi Ouzou]]\n|12 March 2020\n| 15\n| 4\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tipaza Province|Tipaza]]\n|22 March 2020\n|9\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Bordj Bou Arr\u00e9ridj]]\n| 16 March 2020<ref name=\":3\" />\n| 8\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[S\u00e9tif Province|S\u00e9tif]]\n| 19 March 2020\n| 8\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Batna Province|Batna]]\n|25 March 2020\n|8 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scontent-mxp1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/fr/cp0/e15/q65/91518721_865034073969896_2994417577767206912_n.jpg?_nc_cat=104&_nc_sid=110474&efg=eyJpIjoidCJ9&_nc_ohc=Wh3-S-eMznAAX-dw0_h&_nc_ht=scontent-mxp1-1.xx&_nc_tp=14&oh=5ad676cb82c04c7fb1aa920ddead4851&oe=5EA95139|title=Batna|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Tlemcen Province|Tlemcen]]\n|23 March 2020\n|7\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Annaba Province|Annaba]]\n| 17 March 2020<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n| 6\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[M\u00e9d\u00e9a Province|M\u00e9d\u00e9a]]\n|18 March 2020\n| 6\n| 2\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Skikda Province|Skikda]]\n| 12 March 2020\n| 6\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[B\u00e9ja\u00efa Province|B\u00e9ja\u00efa]]\n|17 March 2020<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n| 5\n| 2\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[El Oued Province|El Oued]]\n|18 March 2020\n| 5\n| 2\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Boumerd\u00e8s Province|Boumerd\u00e8s]]\n| 18 March 2020\n| 4\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Bou\u00efra Province|Bouira]]\n|16 March 2020<ref name=\":3\" />\n| 3\n| 0\n| 1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Constantine Province|Constantine]]\n|23 March 2020\n|3\n|3\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Mascara Province|Mascara]]\n| 5 March 2020\n| 3\n| 0\n| 2\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Mostaganem Province|Mostaganem]]\n|25 March 2020\n|3\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Adrar Province|Adrar]]\n| 15 March 2020<ref name=\":2\" />\n| 2\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ain Defla Province|Ain Defla]]\n|24 March 2020\n|2\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[El Taref Province|El Taref]]\n|26 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Guelma Province|Guelma]]\n|26 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Jijel Province|Jijel]]\n|22 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Khenchela Province|Khenchela]]\n| 20 March 2020\n| 2\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Oum El Bouaghi Province|Oum El Bouaghi]]\n|25 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Relizane Province|Relizane]]\n|23 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Sidi Bel Abbes Province|Sidi Bel Abbes]]\n|23 March 2020\n|2\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Souk Ahras Province|Souk Ahras]]\n| 12 March 2020\n| 2\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Ain Temouchent Province|Ain Temouchent]]\n|23 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Biskra Province|Biskra]]\n|25 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Chlef Province|Chlef]]\n|22 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Djelfa Province|Djelfa]]\n|26 March 2020\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| a